gs**.\n3. Under the **Account Info** tab, locate the **Display Name** field.\n4. Enter your desired new display name. You can use spaces and a wider variety of characters than in usernames.\n5. Click the **Save** button to confirm the change.\n\nRemember, your new display name will be visible to other players across Roblox games and your profile, but your original username remains the same for login purposes.\n\n<h3>Display Name Rules and Tips<\/h3>\n\nRoblox has some guidelines that your display name must follow:\n\n- It cannot be offensive or violate Roblox’s community standards.\n- You can only change your display name once every 7 days.\n- Display names are not unique; multiple users can have identical display names.\n\nBecause display names are flexible and free to change, this is usually the best first step if you want a fresh identity without hassle.\n\n<h2>How to Change Your Username in Roblox<\/h2>\n\nIf you’re set on changing your username, which is the permanent login name, there is a way—but it comes with conditions and costs.\n\n<h3>Steps to Change Your Roblox Username<\/h3>\n\n1. Log into your Roblox account on the website.\n2. Click the gear icon in the top-right corner and select **Settings**.\n3. In the **Account Info** tab, find the **Username** section.\n4. Click the **Edit** button next to your username.\n5. Enter your new desired username.\n6. Pay the fee (usually 1,000 Robux).\n7. Confirm the change.\n\n<h3>Important Things to Know About Changing Your Username<\/h3>\n\n- Changing your username costs 1,000 Robux, Roblox’s virtual currency, so make sure you have enough Robux before attempting to switch names.\n- Your new username must be unique and adhere to Roblox’s naming rules, which means no spaces, no offensive language, and only alphanumeric characters and underscores.\n- You can only change your username once every 30 days.\n- After changing your username, your old username becomes available for others to claim, so consider this carefully 